VALUES
(44, 14, 26, 51, 4, 17, 17, NULL, 'Ministry Fulfillment Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of fulfilling one''s ministry. Both passages emphasize the importance of completing the work received from God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 26, 48, 2, 11, 11, 'Antioch', 'Connection through Antioch', 'Both passages emphasize Antioch as a significant location for early Christian activity. Acts 14:26 mentions the completion of a work from Antioch, while Galatians 2:11 highlights a confrontation involving Peter at the same place.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 27, 46, 16, 9, 9, 'opened the door of faith unto the Gentiles', 'Opening of Doors in Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of God opening doors for ministry. Both passages emphasize the idea of an ''opened'' door, indicating opportunities for spreading faith despite challenges.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 27, 44, 15, 12, 12, 'opened the door of faith unto the Gentiles', 'Connection of Gentile Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the work of God among the Gentiles. Acts 14:27 mentions how God opened the door of faith, while Acts 15:12 highlights the miracles and wonders performed among them.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 27, 47, 2, 12, 12, 'opened the door of faith', 'Opening of Faith and Doors', 'This connection highlights the theme of God opening doors for the spread of the gospel. Both passages emphasize how God facilitates opportunities for preaching and faith, specifically to the Gentiles in Acts and to Paul in 2 Corinthians.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 27, 51, 4, 3, 3, 'opened the door of faith', 'Opening Doors of Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of God opening doors. In Acts, it refers to the door of faith for the Gentiles, while in Colossians, it speaks of a door of utterance for proclaiming Christ.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 27, 46, 5, 4, 4, 'gathered the church together', 'Gathering of the Church', 'This connection highlights the theme of gathering the church together in both passages. Acts 14:27 emphasizes the gathering to share God''s work, while 1 Corinthians 5:4 focuses on gathering in the name of Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 27, 43, 9, 10, 10, 'opened the door of faith', 'Opening of Eyes and Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine intervention in opening eyes to faith. In Acts, God opens the door of faith to the Gentiles, while in John, the question of how eyes were opened suggests a miraculous act of revelation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 27, 44, 11, 18, 18, 'opened the door of faith unto the Gentiles', 'Connection of Gentile Faith', 'Both passages emphasize God''s action towards the Gentiles. Acts 14:27 mentions ''opened the door of faith,'' while Acts 11:18 states God granted ''repentance unto life'' to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 28, 44, 11, 26, 26, 'with the disciples', 'Discipleship and Community in Antioch', 'This connection highlights the theme of discipleship and community as both passages reference the gathering of disciples in Antioch. In Acts 11:26, the assembly of disciples is emphasized, while Acts 14:28 mentions their prolonged stay with the disciples, indicating a continuity of teaching and fellowship.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 28, 44, 15, 35, 35, 'with the disciples', 'Continuity of Teaching Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the ongoing ministry of Paul and Barnabas. In Acts 14:28, they are with the disciples for a long time, and in Acts 15:35, they continue teaching and preaching in Antioch.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 1, 48, 5, 6, 6, 'Except ye be circumcised after the manner of Moses', 'Circumcision and Faith Connection', 'This connection highlights the debate over circumcision as a requirement for salvation. Both passages emphasize that faith, rather than circumcision, is what truly matters in Christ.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 1, 44, 15, 5, 5, 'ye cannot be saved', 'Circumcision and Salvation Debate', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of circumcision for salvation. They reflect the ongoing debate among early believers regarding adherence to the law of Moses.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 1, 3, 12, 3, 3, 'be circumcised after the manner of Moses', 'Connection of Circumcision Requirements', 'This connection highlights the requirement of circumcision in both passages. Acts 15:1 discusses the necessity of circumcision for salvation, while Leviticus 12:3 specifies the act of circumcision on the eighth day.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 1, 51, 2, 8, 8, 'ye cannot be saved', 'Connection of Legalism and Deceit', 'This connection highlights the warning against legalistic teachings that can lead believers away from Christ. Both passages emphasize the danger of adhering to human traditions and rules, which can undermine true faith and salvation.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 1, 45, 4, 8, 12, 'ye cannot be saved', 'Circumcision and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between circumcision and faith. Acts 15:1 presents the requirement of circumcision for salvation, while Romans 4:8-12 argues that righteousness is granted through faith, independent of circumcision.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 1, 46, 7, 18, 19, 'ye cannot be saved', 'Circumcision and Salvation Debate', 'This connection highlights the debate over circumcision and its relevance to salvation. Both passages emphasize the idea that circumcision is not necessary for salvation, focusing instead on the importance of keeping God''s commandments.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 1, 48, 2, 11, 14, 'Except ye be circumcised after the manner of Moses', 'Circumcision and Gentile Relations', 'Both passages emphasize the issue of circumcision and its implications for salvation and fellowship among Jews and Gentiles. Acts 15:1 introduces the requirement of circumcision for salvation, while Galatians 2:11-14 illustrates the tension it creates in Peter''s behavior towards Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 44, 15, 22, 23, 'Paul and Barnabas, and certain other of them, should go up to Jerusalem', 'Council Decision and Communication', 'This connection highlights the decision made by Paul and Barnabas to go to Jerusalem, which leads to the apostles and elders sending chosen men back to Antioch. Both passages emphasize the involvement of the apostles and elders in addressing the question of the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 44, 15, 6, 7, 'no small dissension and disputation', 'Disputation and Decision-Making', 'This connection highlights the theme of disputation as both passages describe significant discussions among the apostles regarding the inclusion of Gentiles. The phrase ''much disputing'' in the target passage reflects the earlier ''no small dissension and disputation'' in the source, emphasizing the seriousness of the matter at hand.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 48, 2, 1, 2, 'go up to Jerusalem', 'Journey to Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize a journey to Jerusalem where important discussions about the gospel took place. Acts 15:2 describes the decision to go to Jerusalem, while Galatians 2:1-2 recounts Paul''s visit to communicate the gospel he preaches.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 47, 11, 5, 5, 'no small dissension and disputation', 'Apostolic Authority and Disputes', 'This connection highlights the theme of apostolic authority and the disputes surrounding it. In Acts, Paul and Barnabas engage in significant debate regarding doctrine, while in 2 Corinthians, Paul asserts his standing among the apostles.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 48, 1, 6, 10, NULL, 'Gospel Integrity and Disputes', 'This connection highlights the concern over maintaining the true gospel. Both passages emphasize the importance of not being removed from the original message and the consequences of preaching a different gospel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 2, 18, 23, 23, NULL, 'Leadership and Guidance in Conflict', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking guidance in times of dispute. Both passages emphasize the importance of consulting leaders to ensure peace and order among the people.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 9, 8, 7, 7, NULL, 'Rejection of Authority Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejection of authority. In Acts, the dispute arises over the acceptance of new practices, paralleling the rejection of God''s reign in 1 Samuel.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 3, 44, 14, 27, 27, 'declaring the conversion of the Gentiles', 'Joy in Gentile Conversion', 'Both passages emphasize the conversion of the Gentiles and the resulting joy within the church. Acts 15:3 mentions the joy caused by declaring the conversion, while Acts 14:27 highlights how God opened the door of faith to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 3, 44, 21, 5, 5, 'brought on their way by the church', 'Journey and Community Support', 'Both passages emphasize the communal aspect of travel and support within the church. In Acts 15:3, the church brings Paul and Barnabas on their way, while in Acts 21:5, the community accompanies the travelers, highlighting the joy and unity among believers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 3, 45, 15, 24, 24, 'being brought on their way', 'Journey and Support in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being ''brought on their way'' by the church, highlighting the communal support in ministry journeys. This connection illustrates the importance of fellowship and encouragement among believers as they undertake missions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 3, 46, 16, 6, 6, NULL, 'Journey and Community Support', 'This connection highlights the theme of communal support in the journeys of early Christians. Both passages emphasize the idea of being brought on a journey by the community, reflecting the importance of fellowship in their missions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 3, 56, 3, 13, 13, NULL, 'Journey and Support of Messengers', 'This connection highlights the theme of supporting and sending messengers on their journeys. Both passages emphasize the importance of providing for those who spread the message, fostering joy and diligence in their missions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
